Subject:[edmug] Creating your own Fusion Drive
Apple's official line is that Fusion Drive ( =
http://www.apple.com/uk/imac/features/#storage ) is only available on =
new iMacs and Macs mini, but interestingly with a bit of command line =
wizardry you can in fact set up your own:

=
http://arstechnica.com/apple/2012/10/more-on-fusion-drive-how-it-works-and=
-how-to-roll-your-own/

I'm assuming this only works on Mountain Lion, and obviously you need a =
Mac that can hold both a regular hard drive and an SSD.=
